Card only, cash not accepted. That is a basic (and in the state of New York currently still legal) discrimination against people who have some money in their pocket, but don't possess or don't qualify for a credit or debit card. A new spin on a  time honored technique of exclusion by finance, it used to be called "keeping out the riff raff". Disgusting practice, I will not be going back.

This is pretty much a sister of Chipotle, it just offers some healthier options like farro grain instead of brown rice and squash mushroom mix. Other than that, everything is the same. I got their summer vegetable plato (equivalent to Chipotle’s veggie bowl.) Their tomato salad is not as great as Chipotle and they charge extra for their chips whereas at Chipotle you can get a side of hard shells tacos at no extra cost. I say Chipotle gives you more bang for your buck (especially with the free guacamole with the vegetarian bowl) but you can give this a one time try!
